<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="591" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d591">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.516/56.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Blanchard</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 23, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Please forward the following message to Wehrhane care of Hallgarten and
                            Company, New York: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Justice of peace wanted to execute order of judge of instruction
                                    ordering removal of seal and transportation funds to another
                                    banking house, have declared funds property of bank and
                                    depositors (not) to permit their removal.</p>
                                <p rend="right">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Williams.</hi>
                                </p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>